Cholera - Sri Lanka (06) 980911230522]
Date: Fri, 18 Sep 1998 17:40:51 -0500
From: Clyde Markon <docmarkon@worldnet.att.net>
Source: Daily News - Lakehouse Sri Lanka; Fri 18 Sep 1998
184 cholera patients have been reported from Polonnaruwa and Ampara
districts, Health Ministry sources said. Cholera cases have been reported
from Thamankaduwa, (72 patients), Dimbulagala (25), Hingurakgoda (7)
and Lankapura (9) in the Polonnaruwa district, and from Ampara (46) and
Dehiattakandiya (26) in the Ampara district.
The sources said that 34 patients had died of cholera this year, out
of 938 confirmed cases. They said the Ministry has launched an
accelerated campaign to prevent the spread of cholera to other parts
of the island.
..............................jw
